    "Figure 4d further shows discordant Illumina reads (colored), indicating multiple translocations instead of the actual Alu insertions, which we reported previously 28.",
    "Figure 4e shows another example of a mosaic deletion, this time overlapping an intron of the RBFOX3 gene, which encodes NeuN, a nuclear antigen used for sorting neuronal nuclei 58, 59.",
    "On manual inspection of the short reads (Supplementary Fig. 7), we observed this deletion also on the Illumina reads (five reads out of ∼85×), but it was not identifiable using Manta.",
    "Figure 4d,e also shows the result of PCR validation of both SVs.",
    "For the first validated SV (4D), the PCR gel shows both the insertion and deletion event (column b) with the proper SV length of 240 bp reported by Sniffles2."
